---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const updated = 'May 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy & Cookie Policy"
  description="How the ParkerTech website handles your information and cookies."
>
  <header class="legal-header">
    <div class="container legal-header-inner">
      <a class="brand" href="/#top" aria-label={`${site.brand} — home`}>
        <span class="brand-word">Parker<span class="brand-accent">Tech</span></span>
      </a>
      <a class="legal-back" href="/#top">← Back to site</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main id="main" class="legal">
    <div class="container legal-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <div class="legal-body">
        <p class="legal-lead">
          This policy explains how the ParkerTech website (parkertech.co.uk)
          handles your information. It covers this website only — the products
          listed on it, such as ParkerMarker and VocMark, are separate services
          with their own terms and privacy policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          ParkerTech is a small educational-technology business run by Joseph,
          and is the data controller for this website. For any privacy question,
          email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>When you use the contact form</strong> — your name, email
            address and the message you write.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>When you accept analytics</strong> — if you accept the
            cookie banner, Google Analytics collects anonymous usage data: the
            pages you view, your approximate region, your device and browser
            type, and how you arrived at the site.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Automatically</strong> — like any website, our host receives
            technical data such as your IP address and browser type as a
            standard part of delivering the page.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we use it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact form data</strong> is used only to read and reply to
            your enquiry. You are not added to any mailing list, and it is not
            sold or shared for marketing.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics</strong> are used only to understand which parts of
            the site are useful and to improve it. The data is looked at in
            aggregate and is not used to identify you personally.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This site sets <strong>no cookies unless you accept analytics</strong>
          via the banner shown on your first visit.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            If you <strong>accept</strong>, Google Analytics sets cookies (such
            as <code>_ga</code>) to recognise return visits and measure usage.
            They expire after up to two years.
          </li>
          <li>
            If you <strong>decline</strong> (or ignore the banner), no analytics
            cookies are set and nothing is tracked.
          </li>
          <li>
            Your choice itself is saved in your browser's local storage — not a
            cookie — so the banner doesn't ask again. You can change your mind at
            any time by clearing this site's data in your browser; the banner
            will then reappear.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Services we rely on</h2>
        <p>
          A few trusted third parties help run the site. Each only receives the
          data needed to do its job:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Web3Forms</strong> — delivers contact-form submissions to our inbox.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — website analytics, only with your consent.</li>
          <li><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> — hosts the website.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — serves the site's fonts.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact emails</strong> are kept only as long as needed to
            deal with your enquiry and any follow-up, then deleted.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics data</strong> is retained by Google according to
            the property's settings (by default, up to 14 months).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under UK GDPR you can ask to see, correct or delete the personal data
          we hold about you, object to how it's used, or withdraw your consent.
          Just email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>. If you're
          unhappy with how we've handled your data, you can also complain to the
          Information Commissioner's Office at
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          This website is aimed at school staff and decision-makers, not
          children, and we don't knowingly collect data from children through
          it.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top shows
          when it was last revised.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── header ── */
  .legal-header {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    height: var(--nav-h);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: rgba(19, 19, 24, 0.8);
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(1.3);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(1.3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .legal-header-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .brand {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1.32rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
  }
  .brand-accent {
    background: linear-gradient(120deg, #a294ff, #7d68ff);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    color: transparent;
  }
  .legal-back {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    transition: color 0.2s var(--ease);
  }
  .legal-back:hover {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* ── content ── */
  .legal {
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5.5rem) clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem);
  }
  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 3.1rem);
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }
  .legal-updated {
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .legal-body {
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }
  .legal-lead {
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .legal-body p {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal-body ul {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.7rem;
  }
  .legal-body li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .legal-body li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.62em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .legal-body strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal-body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 5px;
    background: var(--fill-strong);
    color: var(--accent-bright);
  }
  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--accent-bright);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal-body a:hover {
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
